{
  "stem": "13198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know, I used to make them toys out of bits of string or try and get a-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] well-- they-- I don't know how they really came out so well.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because none of them have got any phobias.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I never taught them to hate the Germans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because I didn't believe that that was a good thing, to hate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That-- you don't achieve anything by hatred.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You only get things more and more in a muddle.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So you-- you don't have to love them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But you can ignore them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It's about the best you can do without upsetting your own emotions.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And children can-- you know, they get something that they're all together with other children, and they make their own lives, and their own games.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the little one was, of course, only about four when-- and the others were six and nine.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they were in a different group, for older children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, there were other children, young kids, the same age as [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Carol, ?] who was then four.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But gradually he was five.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then of course, when he first went in-- big tears, because he was only five.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the five-year-olds weren't allowed to wear a-- didn't have to wear the star.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the others, who were older-- they were made to wear the star.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Carol, ?] because he didn't get the star and the others did, considered it a great insult, and began crying, because he didn't get the star to wear.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He had to wait a whole year before he was allowed to wear the star, which I made it, as if it was a great honor, you see, not as an insult.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
